statements: SELECT * FROM attendee_demographics;
SELECT first_name, last_name, age FROM attendee_demographics WHERE gender='Male';
SELECT attendee_id, first_name, last_name FROM attendee_demographics ORDER BY last_name ASC;
SELECT gender, COUNT(*) AS count FROM attendee_demographics GROUP BY gender;
SELECT * FROM attendee_demographics WHERE age > 30 ORDER BY age DESC, last_name ASC;
SELECT * FROM attendee_demographics;

SELECT attendee_id, first_name, last_name FROM attendee_demographics WHERE age BETWEEN 25 AND 40 ORDER BY first_name, last_name ASC;

SELECT a.name, e.event_name, af.rating, af.comments FROM attendees a JOIN attendee_feedback af ON a.attendee_id = af.attendee_id JOIN events e ON e.event_id = af.event_id WHERE af.rating >= 4 ORDER BY af.rating DESC;

SELECT * FROM event_attendees;

SELECT e.full_name, e.age, s.session_name, f.rating FROM event_attendees e JOIN event_sessions s ON e.attendee_id = f.attendee_id JOIN event_feedback f ON f.session_id = s.session_id WHERE f.rating > 4;
SELECT t.ticket_type, t.ticket_price, a.full_name FROM event_tickets t JOIN event_attendees a ON t.attendee_id = a.attendee_id WHERE t.ticket_price > 50 ORDER BY t.ticket_price DESC;
